summary: Completed comprehensive testing of CareQuo insurance platform. Backend APIs are 100% functional, but frontend has authentication session management issues preventing full workflow testing.

ui_bugs.issue: Users get redirected to landing page when navigating to protected routes after successful login
Employees cannot submit claims - returns 404 error because employee profile must be created first

integration_issues.issue: JWT tokens appear to expire quickly or not persist properly across page navigation
Employee users need admin to create their employee profile before they can submit claims or book services

issues: React setState warning in console during navigation

passed_tests: Landing page loads with all feature cards
User registration for all roles (company_admin, hr_manager, employee, super_admin)
All backend API endpoints (20/20 tests passed)
action_item_for_main_agent: Fix authentication session management - JWT tokens are not persisting properly across page navigation, causing users to be redirected to landing page. Also fix employee workflow by ensuring employees can submit claims without requiring separate employee profile creation.
